        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.26697" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The price per kg of soybean is considered for the years 2014-2021 for the US. A weighted average of the price of this crop between all the producing states of the US of this crop was done, based on the production volume shares of the states producing this crop. The values were retrieved in $/BU [1] and converted into $/kg considering a conversion factor of 1/27.22 [2]. References: [1] US Department of Agriculture (NASS), Quickstat, TabLe "SOYBEANS - PRICE RECEIVED, MEASURED IN $ / BU", accessed on 25.08.2023, available at: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/ [2] https://www.rayglen.com/grain-conversion-calculator/
The prices were converted to EUR based on the annual exchange rates published by the European Central Bank (https://sdw.ecb.europa.eu/quickview.do?SERIES_KEY=120.EXR.A.AUD.EUR.SP00.A, last accessed on 2023-06-01) and adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).</comment>
        </property>
